---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Aetheria">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <div class="kicker" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);color:var(--violet-bright);letter-spacing:0.16em;text-transform:uppercase">About</div>
      <h1 style="font-size:2.6rem;margin-top:8px">Half engineer, half world-builder.</h1>
      <p class="lede muted" style="font-size:1.15rem">
        I’m Amara — a creator who builds games you can play in a browser, AI systems that
        run on your own machine, and magical tools that make building feel like spellcraft.
      </p>

      <h2>What I do</h2>
      <p>I move between three kinds of making, and they feed each other:</p>
      <ul class="muted">
        <li><strong>Games</strong> — cozy, haunted, and alive. Single-file HTML5 worlds and agentic engines where NPCs are autonomous.</li>
        <li><strong>AI / agent systems</strong> — local-first, privacy-respecting agents and orchestration. No data leaves your machine unless you say so.</li>
        <li><strong>Creative tools & systems thinking</strong> — browsers, personas, provenance tech, and the connective tissue between worlds.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why this hub exists</h2>
      <p>
        Most of my work is scattered across many repositories. This is the one place it
        converges — polished games, in-progress experiments, and ideas still forming in the
        dark. I believe unfinished work is worth showing, as long as it’s honestly labelled.
      </p>

      <h2>How I like to work</h2>
      <p>
        Build in public. Local-first by default. Magical but legible. I’d rather ship something
        alive that you can open right now than a perfect thing that stays hidden.
      </p>

      <div class="cta-row" style="margin-top:24px">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:natorretti11@gmail.com">Work with me</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/Mellowambience" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
